# serializer version: 1
# name: test_root_help_snapshot
  '''
  Usage: yaya [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGS]...
  
  yaya — a Python agent.
  
  +- Options ---+
  | --json Emit machine-readable JSON to stdout instead of rich text.
  | --verbose -v INTEGER Increase log verbosity (-v info, -vv debug). [default: 0]
  | --quiet -q Suppress all log output.
  | --log-level TEXT Override log level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR). Defaults to config.
  | --version Print version and exit.
  | --install-completion Install completion for the current shell.
  | --show-completion Show completion for the current shell, to copy it or customize the installation.
  | --help -h Show this message and exit.
  +---+
  +- Commands ---+
  | hello Kernel smoke-test: boot, round-trip one event, shut down.
  | serve Boot the yaya kernel and wait for shutdown.
  | update Check for and apply updates from GitHub releases.
  | version Print the installed version.
  | config Inspect resolved yaya configuration.
  | plugin Manage installed plugins.
  | session Manage session tapes (persisted append-only event log).
  +---+
  
  '''
# ---
# name: test_update_help_snapshot
  '''
  Usage: yaya update [OPTIONS]
  
  Check for and apply updates from GitHub releases.
  
  +- Options ---+
  | --check Only check, do not install.
  | --skip Skip the current latest version.
  | --help -h Show this message and exit.
  +---+
  
  Examples: yaya update --check yaya update --check --json yaya update --skip yaya update
  
  '''
# ---
